premise_source_doc_sentence: It is not necessary for these phonemes to include the distinctive feature -LSB- − round -RSB- , because all -LSB- − back -RSB- vowels are -LSB- − round -RSB- vowels , so the roundness feature is not distinctive for front vowels .
Another precursor to feature geometry was proposed by Roger Lass in 1976 , in which he proposed a laryngeal feature submatrix within a distinctive feature matrix .
In linguistics , a distinctive feature is the most basic unit of phonological structure that may be analyzed in phonological theory .
